                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>There is no columetric layout of text</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#Inside front cover" facs="001">Fols. Inside,, </locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> by the angels <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#Inside back cover" facs="104">Fols. Inside,, </locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#53v" facs="054">fols. 53v, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#58v" facs="059">58v, </locus> (multiple full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#65r #94v #96r" facs="066 095 096">65r, 94v, 96r</locus> (line of alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Prepared for tourist economy. The cover has inlaid, carved bone or ivory pieces. There is a heavy leather spine strap. See the same characteristics for EMIP codices 180, 231, 298, 328, and 337
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    EMIP 323 and 328 were produced by splitting one <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</ref> in half.
                    This codex contains the second half of the Psalter. <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMIP00328">Portland, Ethiopic Manuscript Imaging Project, Weiner Codex 138</ref> contains the first half of the Psalter
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#100v #101v #102r #102v #103r #103v" facs="101 102 103 104">Fols. 100v, 101v, 102r, 102v, 103r, 103v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#101r" facs="101"> f. 101r, upper</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    note of secondary ownership: Wǝhibä Sǝllase, Amätä Mädhǝn, Fǝqǝrtä Maryam, Bäträ Maryam and Śahlä Maryam
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#101r" facs="101"> f. 101r, lower</locus>
                    <desc>
                    the remains of a seal
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#23r" facs="023">Fol. 23r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#23v" facs="024">Fol. 23v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#91r" facs="091">Fol. 91r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#9r #13r" facs="009 013">Fols. 9r, 13r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex (throughout) But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to boards recently fashioned of the traditional wood stained black and with bone or ivory inlaid pieces on front and back.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="other">bone or ivory</material>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
